32#ifndef _LINUX_MUTEX_H_
33#define _LINUX_MUTEX_H_
34
35#include <sys/mutex.h>
36
37#include <lib/libkern/libkern.h> /* KASSERT */
38#include <linux/list.h>
39
40#define __acquires(lock) /* XXX lockdep stuff */
41#define __releases(lock) /* XXX lockdep stuff */
42#define might_lock(lock) do {} while(0) /* XXX lockdep stuff */
43
44struct mutex {
45 kmutex_t mtx_lock;
46};
47
48struct lock_class_key {
49};
50
51/* Name collision. Pooh. */
52static inline void
53linux_mutex_init(struct mutex *mutex)
54{
55 mutex_init(&mutex->mtx_lock, MUTEX_DEFAULT, IPL_NONE);
56}
57
58/* Lockdep stuff. */
59static inline void
60__mutex_init(struct mutex *mutex, const char *name __unused,
61 struct lock_class_key *key __unused)
62{
63 linux_mutex_init(mutex);
64}
65
66/* Another name collision. */
67static inline void
68linux_mutex_destroy(struct mutex *mutex)
69{
70 mutex_destroy(&mutex->mtx_lock);
71}
72
73static inline void
74mutex_lock(struct mutex *mutex)
75{
76 mutex_enter(&mutex->mtx_lock);
77}
78
79static inline int
80mutex_lock_interruptible(struct mutex *mutex)
81{
82 mutex_enter(&mutex->mtx_lock); /* XXX */
83 return 0;
84}
85
86static inline int
87mutex_trylock(struct mutex *mutex)
88{
89 return mutex_tryenter(&mutex->mtx_lock);
90}
91
92static inline void
93mutex_unlock(struct mutex *mutex)
94{
95 mutex_exit(&mutex->mtx_lock);
96}
97
98static inline bool
99mutex_is_locked(struct mutex *mutex)
100{
101 return mutex_owned(&mutex->mtx_lock);
102}
103
104static inline void
105mutex_lock_nest_lock(struct mutex *mutex, struct mutex *already)
106{
107
108 KASSERT(mutex_is_locked(already));
109 mutex_lock(mutex);
110}
111
112#define __lockdep_used __unused
113#define lockdep_assert_held(m) do {} while (0)
114#define lockdep_is_held(m) 1
115
116#define SINGLE_DEPTH_NESTING 0
117
118static inline void
119mutex_lock_nested(struct mutex *mutex, unsigned subclass __unused)
120{
121 mutex_lock(mutex);
122}
123
124#endif /* _LINUX_MUTEX_H_ */
